skyislands.command.help.1: /skyislands lobby - teleports the user to the lobby island
skyislands.command.help.2: /skyislands home <player> - teleports the specified player to their island, creating an island if they don't have one (in single player use the lobby subcommand)
skyislands.command.help.3: /skyislands regen <player> - creates a new island for the player (even if they already have one) and teleports them to it
skyislands.command.help.4: /skyislands visit <player> - teleports the user to the specified player's island
skyislands.command.help.5: /skyislands team <player> <team> - teleports the player to the team island, creates the island if needed and moves the player to the team
skyislands.command.help.6: /skyislands list - shows the claimed islands in the log
skyislands.command.noskyblock: Player does not have an island
skyislands.command.wrongworld: This is not a skyislands world
